5000|$|On January 29, Clinton {{reached an}} {{agreement}} with Senate leaders, led by Sen. Sam Nunn, chairman <b>of</b> <b>the</b> <b>Senate</b> <b>Armed</b> Forces Committee, to delay until July any changes in policies with respect to military service by gays and lesbians. At a joint news conference with Nunn, Clinton praised Judge Hatter's ruling, which he said had strengthened {{his hand in the}} negotiations: [...] "It makes the practical point I have been making all along." [...] Meinhold appeared on the February 1 cover of Newsweek that carried the headline [...] "Gays and the Military".|$|R
